CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>SELECT Courses.course_name, COUNT(Enrollments.enrollment_id) AS num_students
FROM Courses
LEFT JOIN Enrollments ON Courses.course_id = Enrollments.course_id
GROUP BY Courses.course_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>select courses.course_name, count(enrollments.enrollment_id) as num_students
from courses
left join enrollments on courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id
group by courses.course_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>SELECT Courses.course_name, COUNT(Enrollments.enrollment_id) AS num_students
FROM Courses
LEFT JOIN Enrollments ON Courses.course_id = Enrollments.course_id
GROUP BY Courses.course_id;</s>

left join enrollments on courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id
group by courses.course_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>SELECT Courses.course_name, AVG(Enrollments.enrollment_id) AS avg_enrollments
FROM Courses
LEFT JOIN Enrollments ON Courses.course_id = Enrollments.course_id
GROUP BY Courses.course_id;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);</t><s>SELECT Courses.course_name, MAX(Enrollments.enrollment_id) AS max_enrollment
FROM Courses
LEFT JOIN Enrollments ON Courses.course_id = Enrollments.course_id
GROUP BY Courses.course_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);</t><s>select courses.course_name, max(enrollments.enrollment_id) as max_enrollment
from courses
left join enrollments on courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id
group by courses.course_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>SELECT student_name, course_name FROM Students, Courses, Enrollments
WHERE Students.student_id = Enrollments.student_id
AND Courses.course_id = Enrollments.course_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

where students.student_id = enrollments.student_id
and courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>SELECT course_name, COUNT(DISTINCT Students.student_id) AS num_students
FROM Courses
LEFT JOIN Enrollments ON Courses.course_id = Enrollments.course_id
LEFT JOIN Students ON Enrollments.student_id = Students.student_id
GROUP BY Courses.course_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>select course_name, count(distinct students.student_id) as num_students
from courses
left join enrollments on courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id
left join students on enrollments.student_id = students.student_id
group by courses.course_id;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);</t><s>SELECT course_name, COUNT(DISTINCT Enrollments.student_id) AS num_students
FROM Courses
LEFT JOIN Enrollments ON Courses.course_id = Enrollments.course_id
GROUP BY Courses.course_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);</t><s>select course_name, count(distinct enrollments.student_id) as num_students
from courses
left join enrollments on courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id
group by courses.course_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));

CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name STRING, instructor_name STRING);

CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name STRING, course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>SELECT course_name, COUNT(DISTINCT Enrollments.student_id) AS num_students
FROM Courses
LEFT JOIN Enrollments ON Courses.course_id = Enrollments.course_id
GROUP BY Courses.course_id;</s>

left join enrollments on courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>SELECT student_name, course_name, COUNT(Enrollments.enrollment_id) AS num_enrollments
FROM Students
LEFT JOIN Enrollments ON Students.student_id = Enrollments.student_id
LEFT JOIN Courses ON Enrollments.course_id = Courses.course_id
GROUP BY Students.student_id, Courses.course_id;</s>

from students

left join courses on enrollments.course_id = courses.course_id
group by students.student_id, courses.course_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT REFERENCES Students(student_id), course_id INT REFERENCES Courses(course_id));</t><s>SELECT student_name, course_name, MAX(Enrollments.enrollment_id) AS max_enrollment
FROM Students

LEFT JOIN Courses ON Enrollments.course_id = Courses.course_id
GROUP BY Students.student_id, Courses.course_id;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name VARCHAR(100), student_grade INT)

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE instructors (instructor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, instructor_name VARCHAR(100), instructor_email VARCHAR(100))</t><s>SELECT students.student_id, students.student_name, courses.course_name FROM students JOIN enrollments ON students.student_id = enrollments.student_id JOIN courses ON courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id</s>

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), instructor_name VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name VARCHAR(100), student_grade INT)</t><s>SELECT students.student_id, students.student_name, courses.course_name FROM students JOIN enrollments ON students.student_id = enrollments.student_id JOIN courses ON courses.course_id = enrollments.course_id</s>

CREATE TABLE instructors (instructor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, instructor_name VARCHAR(100), instructor_email VARCHAR(100))</t><s>SELECT instructor_name, instructor_email, COUNT(course_id) AS num_courses FROM courses JOIN instructors ON courses.instructor_name = instructors.instructor_name GROUP BY instructor_name, instructor_email</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name VARCHAR(100), student_grade INT)

CREATE TABLE instructors (instructor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, instructor_name VARCHAR(100), instructor_email VARCHAR(100))</t><s>select instructor_name, instructor_email, count(course_id) as num_courses from courses join instructors on courses.instructor_name = instructors.instructor_name group by instructor_name, instructor_email</s>

CREATE TABLE instructors (instructor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, instructor_name VARCHAR(100), instructor_email VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)</t><s>select instructor_name, instructor_email, count(course_id) as num_courses from courses join instructors on courses.instructor_name = instructors.instructor_name group by instructor_name, instructor_email</s>

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, grade VARCHAR(10))</t><s>select * from students</s>

CREATE TABLE teachers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), subject VARCHAR(50), experience INT)

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)</t><s>SELECT name, subject FROM teachers</s>

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)</t><s>SELECT * FROM courses</s>

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)</t><s>SELECT course_name, start_date, end_date FROM courses</s>

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, grade VARCHAR(10))</t><s>select dept_name, location from departments where location like '%new york%'</s>

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, grade VARCHAR(10))

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))</t><s>SELECT * FROM students JOIN enrollments ON students.id = enrollments.student_id</s>

CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, grade VARCHAR(10))

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)</t><s>select * from students join enrollments on students.id = enrollments.student_id</s>

CREATE TABLE teachers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), subject VARCHAR(50), experience INT)

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))</t><s>SELECT * FROM teachers JOIN courses ON teachers.id = courses.teacher_id</s>

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE teachers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), subject VARCHAR(50), experience INT)

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)</t><s>select * from teachers join courses on teachers.id = courses.teacher_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, grade VARCHAR(10))

CREATE TABLE teachers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), subject VARCHAR(50), experience INT)

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)</t><s>SELECT * FROM students JOIN enrollments ON students.id = enrollments.student_id JOIN courses ON enrollments.course_id = courses.course_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, grade VARCHAR(10))

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)</t><s>select * from students join enrollments on students.id = enrollments.student_id join courses on enrollments.course_id = courses.course_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, grade VARCHAR(10))

CREATE TABLE teachers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), subject VARCHAR(50), experience INT)

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)</t><s>select * from students join enrollments on students.id = enrollments.student_id join courses on enrollments.course_id = courses.course_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE teachers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), subject VARCHAR(50), experience INT)

CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, grade VARCHAR(10))

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(100), teacher_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))</t><s>SELECT * FROM students JOIN enrollments ON students.id = enrollments.student_id JOIN courses ON enrollments.course_id = courses.course_id</s>

CREATE TABLE teachers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), subject VARCHAR(50), experience INT)

CREATE TABLE departments (dept_id INT PRIMARY KEY, dept_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100))</t><s>select * from students join enrollments on students.id = enrollments.student_id join courses on enrollments.course_id = courses.course_id</s>

CREATE TABLE teachers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), subject VARCHAR(50), experience INT)
